               ],
               "date_time": null,
               "isTable": false,
               "imgdesc": "",
               "format": "markdown",
               "PostMention": ""
            },
            {
               "text": "<center><div class=\"first_steps_reflection_parent\"><div class=\"first_steps_reflection question_mark\"><i class=\"fa-solid fa-brain\"></i></div><div class=\"first_steps_reflection\"><b>Reflection 1: On Precision</b><br /><br />When we use a 365-day year, we introduce an error of 6 hours, which is corrected every four years with a 366-day year.<br /><br />If we counted a year as a total number of weeks (7 days each), would we be closer to or farther from the actual length of a year?</div></div></center>",
               "source": null,
               "date_time": null,
               "isTable": false,
               "imgdesc": "",
               "format": "html",
               "PostMention": " "
            }
         ]
